    "body": "`Box<T>` has value semantics just like `T`. The use cases for it revolve around it being pointer-size, because that allows recursive data structures, type erasure (trait objects) and in some cases is useful for moving around large objects cheaply. The old tutorial had good documentation on the semantics and use cases of boxes without getting caught up in the implementation details. I expect anything new to be at least as good as the work that was thrown out without a replacement.\n",
